---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout lang="en" title="Film style" description="Cinematic wedding films with atmosphere. This is how your films will look and feel.">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-cream pt-32">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-6">Style & experience.</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-brand-text max-w-2xl mx-auto">This is how your films will look and feel: cinematic, emotional, honest.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MEDIA BLOCK: Video/Photo Container -->
  <section class="relative bg-brand-warm">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="relative aspect-video bg-brand-cream overflow-hidden">
        <video src="/filmstil.mp4" poster="/filmstil-poster.jpg" autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata" class="w-full h-full object-contain"></video>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WAS EINEN FIRST UP FILM AUSMACHT -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-warm">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-brand-text leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          A wedding film by First Up Weddings is not a classic wedding recording. It is a film with its own narrative, rhythm, and atmosphere that takes you back to the day — not to what happened, but to how it felt.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our approach blends cinematic craft with a documentary eye: no staged scenes, no posed direction. Instead, real moments captured by a camera that observes without interrupting.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WAS EINEN GUTEN HOCHZEITSFILM LEISTET -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-cream">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-center text-brand-dark mb-16">What a great wedding film does</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading text-brand-accent mb-3">Memories that stay alive</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">Photos show how you looked on this day. A film shows how it felt — the laughter, the tears, the voices, the music.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading text-brand-accent mb-3">Moments you missed</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">On your wedding day, you can't be everywhere. The film preserves moments you would otherwise never have seen: your parents' reaction, your friends' gestures.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading text-brand-accent mb-3">Shareable with the people who matter</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">Family who couldn't be there. Friends in other countries. Or your own children, one day. A wedding film is a gift that lasts.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-heading text-brand-accent mb-3">More than a video</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">A cinematic wedding film tells your story with depth and care — not as documentation, but as a film you want to watch again and again.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DER ANSATZ -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-warm">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-center text-brand-dark mb-16">Our approach: companions, not directors.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-4xl font-heading text-brand-accent">01</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-3">Observe, never stage</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">We never re-stage scenes during the wedding itself. We observe, wait for the right moment, and capture it. The best shots happen when you forget we are there.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-4xl font-heading text-brand-accent">02</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-3">Cinematic quality</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">Professional camera gear, natural light, careful composition. Your film has the visual quality of a feature film, not an event video.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-4xl font-heading text-brand-accent">03</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-3">Narrative, not chronology</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">A great film does not retell the schedule of the day. It tells your story with rhythm, dramaturgy, and an atmosphere that distils the whole day.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-4xl font-heading text-brand-accent">04</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-3">Careful post-production</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-text leading-relaxed">Color grading, sound mix, music selection, editing — the film is made in post. This step gets all the time it deserves, so the final piece is right.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FLEXIBLES SETUP -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-cream">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-6">Tailored to your day</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Every wedding is different, and the setup is too — from a quiet single-camera presence to a more elaborate cinematic production with multiple perspectives. In the conversation we figure out together what fits your day and what makes sense. No off-the-shelf solution, always tailored to you. On request, additional photographic frames can be created from within the filmmaking flow.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- VISUELLE IMPRESSIONEN -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-warm">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-center text-brand-dark mb-6">Visual impressions</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text text-center max-w-xl mx-auto mb-16">A feel for the visual language, the atmosphere, and the moments we capture.</p>
      <div class="space-y-4 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Hero -->
        <div class="aspect-[5/2] overflow-hidden bg-brand-cream">
          <img src="/both.jpg" alt="Couple dancing in fog, cinematic atmosphere" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>

        <!-- Ring details -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="aspect-[3/2] overflow-hidden bg-brand-cream">
            <img src="/ring1.jpg" alt="Ring tray with wedding bands, roses and feathers" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="aspect-[3/2] overflow-hidden bg-brand-cream">
            <img src="/ring2.jpg" alt="Close-up of the wedding bands on a crystal-trimmed stand" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Bride + Groom separately -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 items-center">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden bg-brand-cream">
            <img src="/ilayda.jpg" alt="Bride portrait in warm light, a quiet moment" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-2 aspect-[21/9] overflow-hidden bg-brand-cream">
            <img src="/emin.jpg" alt="Groom playing the davul, family and guests clapping" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNATURE FILM -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-cream">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-6">The signature film.</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Depending on your wishes, we craft a compact highlight film or a fuller cinematic narrative of your entire day. You decide what to capture; the cinematic quality and the care stay the same. Optionally complemented by shorter formats: a social media clip, a teaser for your loved ones, or excerpts from the moments closest to your heart. We define the scope and form together.
      </p>
      <a href="/en/investment" class="text-sm text-brand-accent hover:text-brand-accent-hover transition-colors font-heading tracking-wide">More about your film →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BEYOND THE WEDDING DAY -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-warm">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-6">Beyond the wedding day.</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        The wedding day is the heart of it all, but not the only story worth telling. Engagements, proposals, engagement sessions, save-the-date videos: anything that belongs to your story can be captured cinematically. Unlike the wedding day itself, in these separate shoots we work on request with deliberate composition and jointly planned moments — calm, time, and a relaxed atmosphere just for you. Write to us and we'll make it happen.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section-padding bg-brand-cream">
    <div class="container-narrow text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading text-brand-dark mb-6">Ready to tell your story?</h2>
      <p class="text-brand-text max-w-xl mx-auto mb-10">Tell us about your day and we'll show you how your film could look.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-primary">Request a quote</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
